      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Outdoor photograph of a street or a square in front of a building. A smaller core group and a larger crowd are gathered around an open flower-adorned coffin. The greater part of the men are wearing military uniforms. Right behind the coffin there are a man in military uniform and two women in dark urban clothes, wearing dark veils. The coffin is being tilted up by four men in military uniforms, two of them kneeling and two standing.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Lieutenant Nikola Boyadzhiev, son of General Kliment Boyadzhiev, died on 14 February 1915 in the assassination at the Sofia City Casino. King Ferdinand attended the funeral.</ab>
